Material reference - https://spacelift.io/blog/terraform-commands-cheat-sheet#deploy-your-infrastructure

Get help​
terraform -help

terraform fmt -help

Version info​
terraform version

Format code (fmt)​
terraform fmt

terraform fmt --recursive

terraform fmt --diff

terraform fmt --check

Initialize directory (init)​
terraform init

terraform init -get-plugins=false

terraform init -lock=false

terraform init -input=false

terraform init -migrate-state

terraform init -verify-plugins=false

terraform init -upgrade

Modules (get)​
terraform get

terraform get -update

Validate configuration​
terraform validate

terraform validate -json

Test configuration (test)​
terraform test

terraform test -test-directory=tests

terraform test -filter=tests/my_test.tftest.hcl

terraform test -verbose

Plan infrastructure (plan)​
terraform plan

terraform plan -out=

terraform plan -destroy

Apply infrastructure (apply)​
terraform apply

terraform apply -auto-approve

terraform apply -lock=false

terraform apply -parallelism=

terraform apply -var="environment=dev"

terraform apply -var-file="varfile.tfvars"

terraform apply -target="module.appgw.0"

Destroy infrastructure (destroy)​
terraform destroy

terraform destroy -target="module.appgw.0"

terraform destroy --auto-approve

terraform destroy -target="module.appgw.resource[\"key\"]"

Taint / untaint resources​
terraform taint vm1.name

terraform untaint vm1.name

Refresh state (deprecated)​
terraform refresh

Show state / plan (show)​
terraform show

terraform show <path-to-state-or-plan>

State operations (state)​
terraform state

terraform state list

terraform state mv

terraform state pull > state.tfstate

terraform state push

terraform state replace-provider hashicorp/azurerm customproviderregistry/azurerm

terraform state rm

terraform state show

Import resources (import)​
terraform import vm1.name -i id123

Provider information (providers)​
terraform providers

Workspaces (workspace)​
terraform workspace

terraform workspace show

terraform workspace list

terraform workspace select

terraform workspace new

terraform workspace delete

Outputs (output)​
terraform output

terraform output -state=

terraform output -json

terraform output vm1_public_ip

Force unlock​
terraform force-unlock

Login / logout (remote hosts)​
terraform login

terraform login <hostname>

terraform logout

terraform logout <hostname>

Dependency graph (graph)​
terraform graph

terraform graph -plan=tfplan

terraform graph -type=plan

terraform graph -draw-cycles

Expression console (console)​
terraform console

Change directory (run from other dir)​
terraform -chdir="../dev" apply

Shell tab-completion​
terraform -install-autocomplete

If you want, the commands can be formatted into 
